HOUSE BILL 1532 7
1 (d) (1) The Commission shall review the plan of each electric company, each
2 gas company, and the Department to determine whether the plan is adequate and
3 cost–effective in achieving the greenhouse gas emissions reduction targets established by
4 the Commission under §§ 7–223(b) and 7–224(a)(2) of this subtitle.
5 (2) The Commission shall consider any written findings provided by the
6 Maryland Energy Administration, the Department of the Environment, and the Office of
7 People’s Counsel regarding the design and adequacy of the plan.
8 (3) Subject to paragraph (4) of this subsection, in approving, modifying, or
9 denying the plan of an electric company or a gas company, the Commission shall consider:
10 (i) the cost–effectiveness of the residential, commercial, and
11 industrial sector subportfolios by using:
12 1. the primary State jurisdiction–specific test, as developed,
13 updated, or approved by the Commission, to determine the cost–effectiveness of a program
14 or service prospectively, including consideration of:
15 A. participant nonenergy benefits;
16 B. utility nonenergy benefits; and
17 C. societal nonenergy benefits; and
18 2. a total resource cost test to compare the electricity savings
19 and demand reduction targets of the program or service with the results of similar
20 programs or services implemented in other jurisdictions, including:
21 A. participant nonenergy benefits; and
22 B. utility nonenergy benefits;
23 (ii) the impact on rates of each ratepayer class;
24 (iii) the impact on jobs;
25 (iv) the impact on the environment; and
26 (v) the impact on the greenhouse gas emissions reduction targets
27 specified in Title 2, Subtitle 12 of the Environment Article, established by the Commission
28 under §§ 7–223(b) and 7–224(a)(2) of this subtitle.
29 (4) Nonenergy benefits considered under paragraph (3) of this subsection
30 shall be quantifiable and directly related to a program or service.

